name: Web Development
description: Learn the fundamentals of web development, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and responsive design.
syllabus: Week 1: HTML & CSS, Week 2: JavaScript Basics, Week 3: Responsive Design, Week 4: React

name: Data Structures
description: Introduction to data structures such as arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, and graphs.
syllabus: Week 1: Arrays & Linked Lists, Week 2: Stacks & Queues, Week 3: Trees, Week 4: Graphs
prerequisites: Basic programming knowledge in any language

name: Calculus I
description: Introduction to differential and integral calculus.
syllabus: Week 1: Limits, Week 2: Derivatives, Week 3: Integrals, Week 4: Applications

name: Linear Algebra
description: Study of vector spaces, matrices, determinants, eigenvalues, and eigenvectors.
syllabus: Week 1: Matrices, Week 2: Vector Spaces, Week 3: Eigenvalues, Week 4: Applications

name: Organic Chemistry
description: Introduction to the structure, properties, and reactions of organic compounds.
syllabus: Week 1: Hydrocarbons, Week 2: Functional Groups, Week 3: Stereochemistry, Week 4: Reactions

name: Microeconomics
description: Study of the behavior of individuals and firms in making decisions regarding the allocation of resources.
syllabus: Week 1: Supply & Demand, Week 2: Consumer Behavior, Week 3: Production, Week 4: Market Structures

name: World History
description: A comprehensive overview of world history from ancient times to the modern era.
syllabus: Week 1: Ancient Civilizations, Week 2: Middle Ages, Week 3: Renaissance, Week 4: Modern History

name: Introduction to Sociology
description: Introduction to the study of society, social institutions, and social relationships.
syllabus: Week 1: Sociological Theories, Week 2: Social Institutions, Week 3: Socialization, Week 4: Social Change

name: Cognitive Psychology
description: Study of mental processes such as attention, memory, perception, and problem-solving.
syllabus: Week 1: Attention, Week 2: Memory, Week 3: Perception, Week 4: Problem-solving

name: Quantum Mechanics
description: Introduction to the principles and applications of quantum mechanics.
syllabus: Week 1: Wave-Particle Duality, Week 2: Schr√∂dinger Equation, Week 3: Quantum States, Week 4: Applications
